{ in class } c}{\\text{Total words in class } c}$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[scribd](https://www.scribd.com/document/995641899/14-15-NLP-Bernouli-vs-Multinomial-Naive-Bayes)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Only considers "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "present words and their frequencies"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example: Document Classification"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Features: Word frequencies in documents\nDocument A: \"free money free offer\" → free: 2, money: 1, offer: 1\nDocument B: \"hello world how are\" → hello: 1, world: 1, how: 1, are: 1\n\nMultinomial NB learns:\nP(\"free\"|spam) = count(free in spam) / total words in spam"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bernoulli Naive Bayes"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": A Naive Bayes variant specifically for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "binary/boolean features"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that assumes features follow a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bernoulli (binomial) distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Binary data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (0s and 1s)\n- "},